〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 . In thoſe of Caius;
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 , &c. and moſt conſtantly ſo, The mother of the Gods is to be underſtood. Otherwiſe, if the ſpeciall Deity of the place be mentioned, as 〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 in thoſe of Maximine, and 〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 , the God of the place is to be meant ſingle.

And though this went for a great ſecret in the time of Quercetan, yet Gaffarel ſaith, A preſent ce ſecret neſt plus ſi rare;
                        Curioſitez. innoyes. L. 5. N. 9.

                        car Mounſieur de Claves un des excellens Chimiſtes de noſtre temps, le fait voir tous les jours, &c. that now 'tis no ſuch rare matter, for Monſieur de Claves, one of the moſt excellent Chimiſts of theſe dayes, uſeth to make ſhew of this at any time.

